llar metallicity. Comparing the\nobserved cumulative distribution of fractional luminosity to those expected\nfrom a Gaussian distribution, we find that a distribution centered on the Solar\nsystem's value fits well the data, while one centered at 10 times this value\ncan be rejected. This is of interest in the context of future terrestrial\nplanet characterization because it indicates that there are good prospects for\nfinding a large number of debris disk systems (i.e. with evidence of harboring\nthe building blocks of planets) with exozodiacal emission low enough to be\nappropriate targets for an ATLAST-type mission to search for biosignatures.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 15 Jan 2015 21:00:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 21 Feb 2015 23:44:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-23"}
